Cell["\<\
USE, like QUIT, does not require a semicolon.(You can terminate such \
statements with a semicolon if you like; it does no harm.) The USE statement \
is special in another way, too : it must be given on a single line.\
\>", "Item",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.813395444834225*^9, 
  3.8133954485713673`*^9}},ExpressionUUID->"6a5b5a43-aaa9-4ff7-91e4-\
4f8ed2bcb461"],

